Colombia Stocks: Textiles Fabricato, Ecopetrol Rise; Aval Falls

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-02T21:21:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/colombia-stocks-textiles-fabricato-ecopetrol-rise-aval-falls.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.5 percent to 14,316.39, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.5 percent to 1,692.14, as U.S. stocks
fell on a slump in commodity producers that overshadowed
optimism spurred by the death of  Osama bin Laden .  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  ,  Colombia ’s
biggest textile maker, rose as Colombia nears a free trade
agreement with the U.S. and as Venezuela moves forward with
payment of overdue debts to Colombian exporters, said Carlos
Esteban Santiago, analyst at Alianza Valores SA.  The stock gained 3.2 percent to 45.40 pesos in Bogota
trading at 4 p.m. New York time, the highest closing price since
September 2007.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s state-run oil
company, rose 1.1 percent to 3,840 pesos. Colombia said today
the nation’s oil production climbed to 903,000 barrels per day
in April, a monthly record. Ecopetrol accounted for 89 percent
of the production, according to data on the website of the
state-run National Hydrocarbons Agency.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA, Colombia’s
biggest financial holding company, fell 0.4 percent to 1,345
pesos as investors awaited delayed results of the company’s
share issue, said Mauricio Restrepo Del Toro, research director
at brokerage Bolsa y Renta.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
